==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek term ''[[karioklesis]]'' {{rfscript|Greek}} which means "to lovingly and respectfully approach another". Alternatively, a portmanteau of the words ''[[care]]'' and ''[[confront]]''.

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To [[caringly]] [[confront]] an [[individual]]; To [[approach]] someone in [[love]] and [[respect]] and correct them in an [[honoring]] manner.

